22 LOCAL GOVERNMENT FEMA LOAN REIMBURSEMENT FROM PREVIOUS
23 DISASTERS
24 SECTION 1A.3. Units of local governments that received loan funds under Section
25 1.5(1) of S.L. 2018-138 or Section 1.2(3)a. of S.L. 2019-250 to assist with cashflow management
26 while awaiting federal reimbursement, may apply to the Department of Public Safety, Office of
27 Recovery and Resiliency, for forgiveness of any portion, in whole or in part, of the outstanding
28 principal and interest of each loan received if all of the following conditions apply:
29 (1) The unit of local government applied for Public Assistance reimbursement
30 from the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) and that
31 application was denied, in whole or in part.
32 (2) The unit of local government does not have any active appeals or active
33 arbitrations for Public Assistance reimbursement from FEMA.
34 (3) The project worksheet has been closed.
