19 "§ 14-318.2. Child abuse a misdemeanor.
20 (a) Any parent of a child less than 16 years of age, or any other person providing care to
21 or supervision of such child, who inflicts physical injury, or who allows physical injury to be
22 inflicted, or who creates or allows to be created a substantial risk of physical injury, upon or to
23 such child by other than accidental means is guilty of the Class A1 misdemeanor of child abuse.
24 (b) The Class A1 misdemeanor of child abuse is an offense additional to other civil and
25 criminal provisions and is not intended to repeal or preclude any other sanctions or remedies.
26 (c) A parent who abandons an infant less than seven 30 days of age pursuant to
27 G.S. 14-322.3 shall not be prosecuted under this section for any acts or omissions related to the
28 care of that infant."
