25 "§ 105-153.11. Credit for certain real property donations.
26 (a) Credit. Credit; Limitation. – Subject to the limitations in this section, an individual or
27 a pass-through entity that makes a qualified donation of real property located in North Carolina
28 during the taxable year that is useful (i) for forestland or farmland preservation, (ii) for fish and
29 wildlife conservation, (iii) as a buffer to limit land use activities that would restrict, impede, or
30 interfere with military training, testing, or operations on a military installation or training area or
31 otherwise be incompatible with the mission of the installation, (iv) for floodplain protection in a
32 county that, in the five years preceding the donation, was the subject of a Type II or Type III
33 gubernatorial disaster declaration, as provided in G.S. 166A-19.21, as a result of a natural
34 disaster, (v) for historic landscape conservation, or (vi) for public trails or access to public trails
35 is allowed a credit against the tax imposed by this Part equal to twenty-five percent (25%) of the
36 fair market value of the donated property. qualified donation. A pass-through entity must pass
37 through the credit to its owners as required under subsection (f) of this section. The amount of
38 credit allowed to an individual or pass-through entity may not exceed the limitations provided
39 under subsections (e) and (f) of this section. The credit may not be taken for the year in which
40 the qualified donation is made but may be taken for the taxable year beginning during in the
41 calendar year in which the application for the credit becomes effective as provided in subsection
42 (c) of this section.
43 (b) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
